HEADWORD: Macdoine
<hw>Ma`c⟦eacute⟧`doine"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.,
apparently the same word as <ets>Mac⟦eacute⟧doine</ets>
Macedonia.]</ety> <def>A kind of mixed dish, as of cooked vegetables
with white sauce, sweet jelly with whole fruit, mixed diced fruits or
vegetables etc.; served hot or cold;</def> <specif>Also,</specif>
<mark>(fig.)</mark>, <def>a medley.</def>⟦br⟧
